fields.description:
The Asset Migration did not migrate all assets to the Cloudinary (Staging) env which maps to the Acom Dev Kontent Project.  Because of this we will just point to their Prod Acom Kontent project for Resources.  This will require updates in BELLA and the Custom Link env vars to use the Prod Kontent Project.

h3. +ORIGINAL DESCRIPTION+

While testing Resources in Playbooks we discovered the Arthrex.com Kontent Project Resources do not all exist in the Dev Cloudinary environment -> instead some of these resources tie to Production cloudinary assets that use the cdn.arthrex.io secure distribution domain.

The QA Arthrex.com environment checks if the resource contains an aprimoAssetId:

* if it does then the resource is in Prod cloudinary
* if it does not then the resource is in dev -> use res.cloudinary.com/arthrex-dev

This is because not all assets were migrated to Cloudinary for QA env during the asset migration.

fields.customfield_10200:
* Set up SES to notify via Email from our Playbook Worker
** SES deployed via CDK with the rest of our infrastructure
* When a Playbook is Published or Unpublished the worker should notify via Email the following:
** *prod*: [DAM@Arthrex.com|mailto:DAM@Arthrex.com] 
** *qa*: [Shobana.singh@arthrex.com|mailto:MobileDev@arthrex.com] && [mobiledev@arthrex.com|mailto:mobiledev@arthrex.com]
* _Could additionally check our db to verify the playbook wasnt already unpublished before sending email_
* When a Playbook *containing errors* is Published the worker should notify via Email to the same emails listed above
* Email contains
** subject: Kontent Driven Playbooks Notification
** body: 
*** Status update (published / unpublished)  Clarify our Playbook Service is marking it as unpublished if it contained errors and was published
*** Playbook ID
*** Title 
*** and any validation errors found when attempting to publish (_if they exist_)

fields.customfield_10200:
ArthrexMobile PAW file contains groups/endpoints for the following:
* BFF
** repapp -> /playbooks
** bella -> /asset
* Auth & Acom API
** login
** token
** GET /user  
* Kontent Devliery API (both Playbooks and Acom projects)
** would be nice to include preview as envs 
* etc.

nonEditableReason.message: The Parent Link is only available to Jira Premium users.

fields.description:
As a developer I would like to leverage a single PAW file to verify any internal or external API calls to ensure our services and integrations are working properly. We had a PAW file setup in MobileBFF that could be resurrected but this new PAW file should be a global one that contains all APIs and endpoints that our apps and services integrate with such as:
* BFF
* Auth & Acom API
* Kontent Devliery API 
* etc.

* In prod go to InternalBrace > Negotiate
* Expand "Customer: My Brostroms do fine"
